commit.message: Fix function search for stripped binary with separate debug info file
Update cursive (fixes #4)
Add knowledge transfer presentation on wachy internals
Speed up fuzzy search with element_limit

Unify bpftrace Command creation

Will allow us to add env in the future if necessary.

Show more results in search view (fixes #5)

Also fixes sizing to properly display scroll bars.

Update cplus_demangle

To pick up fix for viveksjain/rust_cplus_demangle#1.
Fix refreshing search view immediately

Don't crash when symbol information doesn't exist (fixes #3)

Fixed `Controller::setup_function` (if source mapping doesn't exist) and
`Program::get_symbol`.

Replace some unwraps that should never fail with expect

Eventual goal is to remove all unwraps and fix error handling
everywhere.
Fix outputting message after panic
Update cursive packages
Basic script to generate release artifacts
Update version to 0.1.0-alpha.6

Add support for newer bpftrace (fixes #2)

Seems like bpftrace has changed its parsing/precedence for `+=` vs `-`,
causing errors in some expressions.

Fix docs anchor links

Looks like github has different behavior from VSCode.
Add support for printing mangled function name
Link to blog post
Link to website
Various doc tweaks
Add notice file
Add some small metadata to package with cargo-deb
Mitigation for breakdown with recursive calls, documentation tweaks

Update cargo dependencies

No longer need to refer to local paths in Cargo.toml, upstream versions
have the necessary fixes. Took this as an opportunity to update all
packages, which required updating various library calls too.
Add license
Fix unsetting of filters
Update docs
